The '''SX troop transport''', also called a '''L two hundred''', was a [[Transport/Legends|transport]] used by the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] and later by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] to transport troops. They had broad wings and pointed bows.

These [[Transport/Legends|transports]] were deployed during the [[Battle of Murkhana (Clone Wars)|Battle of Murkhana]] in the closing hours of the war. During the [[Great Jedi Purge/Legends|Great Jedi Purge]] that followed, ten [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] survivors managed to steal a [[Vagabond Trader|transport of this type]] from [[Dellalt/Legends|Dellalt]]. They were pursued by an Imperial light [[Cruiser/Legends|cruiser]] and a number of [[Aggressive ReConnaissance-170 starfighter/Legends|ARC-170 starfighter/bombers]], before being rescued by the ''[[Drunk Dancer]]''.

